    {
      "id": "18f4750c-f3ba-8078-a0d8-f89b5d791b99",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Grouping students often leads to communities, but current criteria for grouping are limited. The paper proposes a framework to group students according to behavior, which allows, in the future, to correctly assign a newcomer - in this case, groups refers to learning communities.. Using a graph-based model, authors use spectral clustering to find fair groups. Authors test their model on both a real and synthetic datasets and outperforms other options.",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
